transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey Raphael, thanks for holding but I did exactly what you wanted and I have my fingerprints.

Speaker 2: On this, so I always take a lot of pride in all of my work. So take down my extension for your reference, it's 0037.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and the name is K.T. Goodrich, K as in King and T as in—

Speaker 2: Tom? Yeah, that's correct. Killer Tomato, Killer Tree Circle, so just call me anytime you need.

Speaker 1: I'll be here and you can use me as a reference. What I did is I put a stop to any and all monthly—

Speaker 2: Shipments, I overrode the system, I put a stop to any and all monthly refills and I definitely put—

Speaker 1: A stop to any and all monthly charges and I paused your prescription and I set it up where in the—

Speaker 2: Future, should you decide to want a refill when you go to scoreblue.com and you log in with your—

Speaker 1: Yahoo account, your Yahoo email, I put a red button with white font that says quick refill.

Speaker 2: Now when you click that to get a refill, it doesn't mean you're going to get it monthly again.

Speaker 1: It just means you want 10 of them, just the same quality.

Speaker 2: That's what I was going to ask you, K.T. Is there any way like when I said with the refills that I've been getting, I got a pretty good amount—

Speaker 1: Of pills but say like six months down the road I just want one month's prescription, I mean—

Speaker 2: Uh, without the monthly, you're just saying that it's possible then?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so what the way it works is the way it works is when you go to scoreblue.com and you log in right—

Speaker 2: With your Yahoo account, you're going to type in right your Yahoo and you go to the category your—

Speaker 1: Prescription and just to answer your question, when you click the quick refill it doesn't mean that—

Speaker 2: You get it monthly, it just means that you get 10 of the same prescription that you wanted and it—

Speaker 1: Doesn't go monthly anymore. The way it's set up is the minimum refills is two refills a year of 20—

Speaker 2: Pills, so sometime next year just click that or whenever you want and then you can get exactly—

Speaker 1: What you want, you have full autonomy. All right, and just know that legally though in the state—

Speaker 2: Of California we're not authorized legally to send you or a refill within 30 days. You can only do—

Speaker 1: One refill within a 30-day period or two refills within a year and that's it. But I put a pause on—

Speaker 2: That in a hold and then you can click that at your leisure. That way you can save the money you need—

Speaker 1: And recover. You have a bunch of pills that you can use at your leisure. Click that button or call me—

Speaker 2: If for some reason these are too strong as you start to use them or they get, you get anticlimactic—

Speaker 1: Call me and I can see what I can do to do a ladder move with something stronger—

Speaker 2: Or something that works because the body does adapt. All right, bud?

Speaker 1: Okay, all right, no I appreciate it. That's gonna say I was going to be the only question I had and you answered. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, use that button or call me but click that so you can get the refills at your leisure.

Speaker 1: You can click it every 30 days, every two months, every three months. All right?

Speaker 2: And that way you have full control. All right, bud?

Speaker 1: Okay, I appreciate it, thank you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you bet, bud, and take care and I wish you all the best.

Speaker 1: All right, call us if you need us.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you, you do the same. Take care.
